{
  "doc_id": "37683",
  "text": "The results reported here also have important practical implications for organizational team management because NFC fosters the beneficial effects of team diversity on team performance [CITATION_1] and is also associated with information search in small group settings [CITATION_2] . As modern organizations are increasingly diverse and most organizational groups are engaged in information sharing and information processing activities, using NFC evaluation in personnel selection, could substantially improve the team staffing practices. The two dimensions (gender and nationality) used in this study to compute the social network variety are particularly relevant as women and immigrants are occupational minorities that received considerable attention because their labor force participation in Europe steadily increased during the last decades. Mass media often depicts women and immigrants as occupational minorities and socially shared negative stereotypes may generate conflicts in the workplace that ultimately decrease group and organizational performance [CITATION_3] . It is therefore important to understand the factors that generate more social integration in social networks and ultimately in the increasingly diverse workplaces.",
